# Tenancy Rules

- Determine context first: **landlord (central)** vs **tenant**.
- Never perform cross-tenant reads/writes unless explicitly central and audited.
- Do not access tenant data before tenancy initialization middleware is active.
- In central flows, avoid tenant-scoped model resolution unless intentionally switching context.
- Tenant lifecycle operations (create/suspend/delete) must be idempotent and safe on retries.
- Any tenant provisioning/deprovisioning must emit auditable events.
